  "texts": [
    "However, enforcing physics through penalty terms increases the computational effort, where the solutions still do not necessarily satisfy the corresponding physical laws.",
    "Instead, enforcing physical laws by construction guarantees that they are obeyed, which is more favorable to adding constraints through penalty terms.",
    "• Simulation enhancement is currently one of the most promising areas of investigation.",
    "It is in particular beneficial for tasks where classical methods show difficulties.An excellent example for this is the formulation of consti-tutive laws, which are inherently phenomenological and thereby well-suited to be identified from data using tools such as deep learning.",
    "In addition, simulation enhancement, makes it possible to draw on insights gained from classical methods developed since the inception of computational mechanics."
